    ## PRD — Email Communications & Notifications (Resend)

**Priority:** 🔴 High  
**Status:** Foundational (required for authentication, onboarding, and client communication)

This PRD defines how the Superwork portal sends **transactional and notification emails** using **Resend**, covering login flows, invitations, and ongoing client notifications.

---

## 1. Purpose & Scope

**Purpose**  
Provide reliable, branded, and secure email communication between Superwork and its users.

Email is required for:
- Authentication (login, password reset)
- Inviting users to organizations
- Notifying customers about project activity
- Communicating billing and account updates

This PRD covers **transactional and system emails only**.

---

## 2. Email Provider

- **Provider:** Resend
- **Email type:** Transactional (no marketing in v1)
- **Delivery requirement:** High reliability and fast delivery
- **Branding:** Superwork branded sender

---

## 3. Sender Identity & Domains

### Sender Configuration
- **From name:** Superwork
- **From email:** `no-reply@superwork.com` (or verified subdomain)
- **Reply-to:** not required in v1 (future: support@)

### Domain Setup
- Domain verified in Resend
- SPF, DKIM, and DMARC configured
- No shared sender domains

**Acceptance criteria**
- Emails land in inbox, not spam
- Domain reputation is protected

---

## 4. Email Types (v1)

### 4.1 Authentication Emails

#### Login / Magic Link (if enabled)
- Trigger: user requests login
- Content:
  - Secure login link
  - Expiration notice
  - Device/IP hint (optional)
- CTA: “Log in to Superwork”

#### Password Reset
- Trigger: user requests password reset
- Content:
  - Reset link
  - Expiration notice
  - Security disclaimer

---

### 4.2 Invitation Emails

#### Organization Invite (Customer → Colleague)
- Trigger: customer admin invites user
- Content:
  - Inviter name
  - Organization name
  - Invite acceptance link
- CTA: “Join [Company] on Superwork”

#### Provider Invite (Admin → Consultant)
- Trigger: admin invites provider
- Content:
  - Role explanation
  - Invite link
- CTA: “Accept invite”

---

### 4.3 Account & Subscription Notifications

#### Welcome Email
- Trigger: new organization created (self-service or admin-created)
- Content:
  - Brief explanation of Superwork
  - Link to portal
  - Next steps

#### Plan Change
- Trigger: subscription plan updated
- Content:
  - Old plan → new plan
  - Effective date

---

### 4.4 Project & Delivery Notifications

#### Project Created
- Trigger: new project added
- Recipients:
  - Customer org members
  - Assigned providers
- Content:
  - Project name
  - Link to project

#### Project Status Update
- Trigger: status changes
- Content:
  - Old status → new status
  - Short message from provider (optional)

---

### 4.5 Asset & Message Notifications

#### New Deliverable Uploaded
- Trigger: asset marked as final
- Content:
  - Project name
  - Download link

#### New Message / Feedback
- Trigger: new comment added
- Content:
  - Author name
  - Project context
  - Link to thread

---

### 4.6 Billing Notifications

#### Invoice Issued
- Trigger: new invoice available
- Content:
  - Invoice number
  - Amount
  - Due date
  - Link to invoice

---

## 5. Notification Rules

### General Rules
- Emails are **opt-outable** per notification category (v2)
- No email spam or activity floods
- Group similar events when possible

### v1 Defaults
- All transactional emails enabled
- No granular notification settings yet

---

## 6. Email Template Requirements

### Design
- Clean, minimal, text-first layout
- Superwork branding
- Works in dark and light email clients
- Accessible (contrast, readable fonts)

### Content Rules
- Clear subject lines
- One primary CTA per email
- Plain language
- No marketing language

---

## 7. Technical Integration

### Backend Requirements
- All emails triggered server-side
- Resend API used via secure environment keys
- Idempotency to prevent duplicate sends
- Logging of email events (sent, failed)

### Data Requirements
Each email must include:
- Recipient user ID
- Related entity ID (org, project, invoice)
- Timestamp

---

## 8. Email Logging & Observability

### Required
- Log all sent emails
- Track failures
- Ability to replay failed sends (admin-only)

### Non-Goals (v1)
- Open tracking
- Click tracking
- Marketing analytics

---

## 9. Security & Compliance

- Tokens in links must:
  - Be single-use
  - Expire
- No sensitive data in email body
- GDPR-compliant handling of personal data

---

## 10. Explicit Non-Goals

- Marketing emails
- Newsletters
- Drip campaigns
- In-app notifications (separate PRD)

---

## 11. Key Acceptance Criteria

- Users receive login and invite emails reliably
- Emails are branded and professional
- No duplicate or spammy notifications
- All critical portal actions have email coverage
- Failed emails are visible to admins

---

## 12. Definition of Done

When this PRD is complete:
- Authentication and onboarding emails work end-to-end
- Customers and providers stay informed without logging in
- The portal feels trustworthy and production-ready
- Email is no longer a blocker for core flows
